mentid=\u00224010230\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204021\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627350871\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257710\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022K^2\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, K^2 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEh. That\u0027s what mods are for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTen internet points from my personal reserves to anyone who manages to implement realistic wormhole rendering in KSP2 mod, such as example shown by \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=V7e-1bRpweo\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003EScott Manley in the 360 Wormhole video\u003C/a\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot sure if that\u0027s even computable by a computer that runs ksp tbh\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"K^2","CreatedById":57710,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-27T02:48:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224010236\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204021\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627351080\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213042\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stratennotblitz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Stratennotblitz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnot sure if that\u0027s even computable by a computer that runs ksp tbh\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you use the same trick he did for caching intermediate results and render it in a shader at a reasonable resolution, you can run it on a good GFX card. Lots of tricky math and good programming exercise, but very doable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOf course, if you want to be able to render a ship in transit, there is an additional challenge, since you can\u0027t just do an honest ray tracing of it. You\u0027d have to utilize screen space information in a clever way. It won\u0027t be perfect, and you\u0027ll definitely have some distortions and smudges on the ship, but if it goes through quickly enough it should look ok. (If anyone is familiar with rendering screen space reflections - yeah, basically same problem.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"pandaman","CreatedById":130621,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-27T06:03:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224010210\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204021\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627347562\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213042\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stratennotblitz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Stratennotblitz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI said per example, it could be a solar flare, asteroid impact etc\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhich is still \u0027random bad luck\u0027 by another name.\u00A0 \u00A0I\u0027m perfectly capable of creating my own \u0027unforseen circumstances\u0027 without help\u00A0from a random die-roll.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow IF the game had ways to detect and warn of said events.\u00A0\u00A0Therefore giving players\u00A0a chance and option\u00A0to avoid or deal with them, then that becomes\u00A0\u0027gameplay\u0027 which I would be ok with (but a little sceptical)\u00A0if it was implemented well enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-07-29T15:17:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224009644\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022204021\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221627258779\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022213042\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Stratennotblitz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 7/26/2021 at 1:19 AM, Stratennotblitz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwormhole\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot familiar with KSP? Kinda goes against the base of the game, fly a rocket and get from A to B while doing cool stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}